# Question 5/100 (🟢 Easy)

## 🎤 Interviewer

> You are given an employee DataFrame with the following columns:
>
> `emp_id`, `name`, `department`, `salary`, `city`
>
> Write PySpark code to perform the following tasks:
>
> 1. Sort the DataFrame by **salary in descending order**.
> 2. Display only the **top 3 highest-paid employees**.
> 3. Sort the DataFrame first by **department (ascending)** and then by **salary (descending)**.
>
> Write clean and readable PySpark code.

---

## Dataset

| emp_id | name  | department | salary | city      |
| ------ | ----- | ---------- | ------ | --------- |
| 101    | John  | IT         | 60000  | Mumbai    |
| 102    | David | HR         | 45000  | Delhi     |
| 103    | Alice | IT         | 70000  | Pune      |
| 104    | Bob   | Finance    | 55000  | Hyderabad |
| 105    | Sam   | HR         | 48000  | Chennai   |

---

